text: Nashville is an unincorporated community in Jackson County, in the U.S. state of Iowa. ==History== Nashville contained a post office from 1871 until 1935. The community was named by an early settler for his native hometown of Nashville, Tennessee. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Jackson County, Iowa Category:1871 establishments in Iowa Category:Populated places established in 1871 Category:Unincorporated communities in Iowa
title: Nashville, Iowa
